name: Butte Public Health
tweet: @cre8iverenewal However, the mandate gives organizations, businesses and education settings more authority to require those who are infected to isolate and those who may have been exposed to quarantine, preventing exposure in these higher-risk public settings.

name: Butte Public Health
tweet: @cre8iverenewal Isolation and quarantine has been required by BCPH since the beginning of the pandemic and has been part of our messaging. The difference now is that it is mandated by Health Officer. For the most part, we will continue to rely on voluntary compliance from the public.

name: Butte Public Health
tweet: @cre8iverenewal Also, any business may require the public to wear a mask. It is strongly recommended that all people, regardless of vaccination status, wear a mask when indoors in public places.

name: Butte Public Health
tweet: @cre8iverenewal At this time, masks are only required for those who remain unvaccinated. There are some situations when wearing a mask is required for everyone, such as on public transportation, at school, at shelters, and in healthcare settings.
